# Vercel hosts only the static frontend + api/index.py (see DEPLOY.md).
# The LiveKit agent worker runs on Railway - none of its heavy dependencies
# or source belong in the Vercel build. Excluding the root requirements.txt
# is the critical line here: without it, Vercel's Python builder picked up
# agent.py's full dependency set (livekit-agents + every STT/TTS/LLM plugin,
# including kittentts's bundled model weights) and produced a 5.3GB bundle
# against Vercel's 500MB function size limit. api/requirements.txt (just
# livekit-api) is the only one Vercel should ever see.
/requirements.txt

# Worker source - never imported by api/index.py, no reason to ship it.
/agent.py
/db_helper.py
/sarvam_wrappers.py
/smallest_wrappers.py
/rumik_wrappers.py
/status_server.py

# Not needed at runtime.
/assets/
/tests/
/scripts/
/data/
/logs/
/CHANGELOG.md
/LATENCY_NOTES.md
/fixed.md
/DEPLOY.md
/Procfile
/railway.json
*.wav
